Naval Ravikant is a well-known entrepreneur, author, and investor. He is known for his insights on business, technology, and personal development. Here are a few YouTube channels and personalities that have similar content to Naval Ravikant:

1. Sam Altman - He is an entrepreneur, startup advisor, and president of Y Combinator. His channel features interviews with entrepreneurs and business leaders, as well as insights on startups and technology.
2. Tim Ferriss - He is an entrepreneur, author, and podcast host. His channel features interviews with successful entrepreneurs and business leaders, as well as information on personal development and achieving success in business.
3. Jason Calacanis - He is an entrepreneur, angel investor, and podcast host. His channel features interviews with successful entrepreneurs and business leaders, as well as insights on startups, technology, and investing.
4. Peter Thiel - He is a venture capitalist, entrepreneur, and author. His channel features interviews with successful entrepreneurs and business leaders, as well as insights on startups, technology, and investing.
5. Patrick O'Shaughnessy - He is an investor, author, and podcast host. His channel features interviews with successful entrepreneurs and business leaders, as well as insights on investing and personal development.
6. Ramit Sethi - He is an entrepreneur, author, and personal finance expert. His channel features advice on personal finance, career development, and entrepreneurship.
7. Naval - his channel features his talks, podcast and interviews on a wide range of topics including business, technology, investing, and personal development.
8. Balaji Srinivasan - He is an entrepreneur, investor and a technology commentator, his channel features talks on technology, startups, and trends.
9. Naval Ravikant's podcast, the "Naval" podcast, features interviews with entrepreneurs and business leaders, as well as insights on technology, startups, and personal development, it's a good way to get more of his content.

These channels and personalities are known for their insights on business, technology, and personal development, and they often feature interviews with successful entrepreneurs and business leaders, as well as insights on startups, technology, investing and personal development.
